<H3> <TI>   11 Mar U.S.-ROK `War Exercise' Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1303083994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0809 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1303083994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 13 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists 
on March 11 staged a war exercise targeted against the North in 
the sky above Kunwi, Yoju and Sangdong, South Korea, with the 
mobilisation of formations of Pacific-based assault planes and 
above 400 fighter-bombers, observation planes and reconnaissance 
planes belonging to the U.S. Air Force present in South Korea 
and the puppet Air Force, according to military sources. 
  On the same day, armed bandits of the puppet Army in Yonchon 
County and Paju County, Kyonggi Province, and Chorwon County and 
Inje County, South Korean Kangwon Province, fired at random 
large-calibre machine gun and automatic rifles toward the 
Demilitarized Zone along the Military Demarcation Line, thus 
whipping up war hysterics. 

</TEXT>

