<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   SKNDF Urges ROK To Abolish Security Law </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1403051894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0457 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1403051894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 14 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the 
Central Committee of the South Korean National Democratic Front 
[SKNDF] (Hanminjon) released a statement on March 10 urging the 
Kim Yong-sam group to abolish the "National Security Law" [NSL] 
and step down from power, the Seoul-based radio Voice of 
National Salvation reported. 
  Recalling that U.S. State Secretary Christopher finally 
confirmed that the demand for the abrogation of the "NSL" in 
South Korea was an official position of the United States, the 
spokesman said: 
  As the whole world admits, the "NSL" is an anti-democratic, 
anti-national and anti-reunification fascist law unprecedented 
in the world history of legislation. 
  It is due to this cursed, murderous law that many champions 
of democracy and reunification and patriotic people of various 
social strata have suffered behind bars and the dialogue, 
cooperation and exchange between the North and the South have 
been blocked. 
  The "NSL" is, indeed, a means for maintaining the fascist 
system and prolonging their days in power, which is worse by far 
than the Japanese imperialists' "Public Peace Law" and is an 
obstacle to great national unity and the country's reunification. 
  The Kim Yong-sam group is now scheming to keep the "NSL" 
intact, discontented with the demand for its abolition. This 
clearly shows that "democratization," "improvement of 
North-South relations" and "resumption of dialogue" which the 
Kim Yong-sam group is crying for are all lies and it, in 
actuality, wants neither the democratization of the South Korean 
society nor reconciliation and dialogue between the North and 
the South. 

</TEXT>

