<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Amnesty Report on Rights in ROK Viewed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1303084494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0833 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1303084494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Deserved Denunciation of `Civilian Fascists'" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 13 (KCNA) -- The report of the 
Amnesty International exposing human rights violations in South 
Korea is a stern condemnation and indictment against the 
strong-arm rule and fascist suppression by the Kim Yong-sam 
group under the veil of "civilian regime" and "reform", says 
MINJU CHOSON today. 
  When he took office, Kim Yong-sam made a noisy advertisement 
as if he would bring something like "reforms" and "changes", but 
nothing has changed, the analyst says, and continues: 
  He has only inherited the ruling system of the preceding 
dictators, more harshly suppressed the people with physical 
strength and made all social evils prevail. 
  The Kim Yong-sam group is now deeply vexed, expressing 
"regret" at the report of the Amnesty International noting that 
the human rights situation has not improved in South Korea. 
  The denunciation of the Kim Yong-sam group by the 
international community is a result of its crimes. It deserves 
that. 
  The Kim Yong-sam clique must step down before it faces 
greater denunciation from the South Korean people and the 
international community. 

</TEXT>

