<F P=103> SK1303084194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 13 (KCNA) -- State commendations 
were awarded to officials in charge of party's ideological work 
on March 12 with a due ceremony in Pyongyang. 
  Kim Il-song Order was awarded to Choe Hak-chol, secretary in 
charge of propaganda of the party committee of the Kim Chaek 
iron and steel complex who had made a great contribution to the 
powerful mobilisation of party members and other working people 
in the implementation of party's policies and to the 
strengthening of the singlehearted unity of the whole society by 
intensifying education in the chuche idea among them, upholding 
the leadership of the party, and citations of the dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il to model officials in charge of party's 
ideological work. 

</TEXT>

