<H3> <TI>   KCNA Reports Release of New Documentary Films </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1503110594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1038 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1503110594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 15 (KCNA) -- The Korean documentary 
film studio has released several documentary films recently. 
  The film "Turn" shows imperishable feats performed by the 
dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il in the ideological field by 
proclaiming the programme of modelling the whole society on the 
chuche idea on February 19, 1974, and bringing about a new turn 
in the party's ideological work. 
  "Embraced in the Bosom of Great Love" shows Yi In-mo living 
a 
happy life with great glory, highly praised by people at home 
and abroad as the incarnation of faith and will, after returning 
home. 
  Yi In-mo goes round significant places of the socialist 
homeland which made a signal development, keenly feeling the 
benevolence of the party and the leader, solicitude of the 
socialist system and the love of the revolutionary comrades. He 
says our leader, our party and our country were the best and he 
is now in an "Earthly Paradise." 
  "Long Live the Great Rural Theses" and "Yongsan-ri Undergoes 
Changes" represent the looks of the countryside that has changed 
beyond recognition thanks to the great socialist rural theses 
and the happiness of the people. "Intimate Feelings of Kinship" 
vividly depicts the true appearance of Korean-style socialism in 
which all the people form a big harmonious family and help and 
lead each other forward. 
  Among the newly released documentary films are also 
"Self-Reliance Is the Spirit of Korea," "Masters of Forests" and 
"Respected People" which introduce the noble spiritual world and 
beautiful traits of honest-minded people who have devoted their 
all to the country, the people, the society, the collective and 
the revolutionary comrades, doing what the party wants. 

</TEXT>

