<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   KCNA Notes `Upswing' in Coal Production </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1403234394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1500 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1403234394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 14 (KCNA) -- An upswing in 
production is effecting at coal mines of Korea. 
  The Sunchon district coal mining complex is now 
overfulfilling its plan of capital tunnelling by 3 percent, 
preparatory tunnelling by 5 percent, sloping pit tunnelling by 4 
percent and coal production by 1.5 percent on a daily average 
compared with the previous month. 
  The Myongchon district coal mining complex is fulfilling its 
coal production at 110 percent on a daily average in March by 
substantially organizing and commanding production and actively 
tapping potential reserves. 
  The Anju, Tokchon and Pukchang district coal mining 
complexes 
are increasing coal production by managing equipment well and 
introducing new blasting methods and coal cutting methods. 
  The February 8 Jiktong Youth, Sinri, Hwasong, Thongchon and 
other coal mines are increasing daily coal production 1.2 times 
as against the same period last year by keeping equipment in 
full capacity operation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

