<F P=102>  BK1303072294 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 1330 GMT 12 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1303072294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rangoon Radio Burma </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Burmese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At the invitation of U Ohn Gyaw, minister of foreign 
affairs of the Union of Myanmar [Burma], a seven-member Cuban 
delegation led by Roberto Robaina Gonzalez, foreign minister of 
the Republic of Cuba, arrived this evening on a Thai 
International flight for a visit to Myanmar. 
  The Cuban foreign minister and delegation were welcomed at 
the airport by Foreign Minister U Ohn Gyaw, Deputy Foreign 
Minister U Nyunt Swe, and high-ranking officials from the 
Ministry of Foreign Affairs. 
  Foreign Affairs Minister U Ohn Gyaw received the visiting 
Cuban foreign minister at Karaweik Hall at 1800 this evening. 
They held a meeting during which they exchanged views on 
matters of bilateral interests in a friendly and cordial manner. 
At the meeting, the Myanmar side was represented by Foreign 
Affairs Minister U Ohn Gyaw, Deputy Foreign Affairs Minister U 
Nyunt Swe, and high-ranking officials, while the Cuban side was 
represented by the visiting Cuban foreign minister and 
delegation. 
  At 1930, Foreign Affairs Minister U Ohn Gyaw hosted a dinner 
for the esteemed guests. 

