<H3> <TI>   Meets Officials, Departs 14 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1403154394 </F>
<F P=103> BK1403154394 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese at 1330 
GMT on 14 March provides several reports on the activities of 
Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina Gonzalez during his visit 
to Burma. 
  Senior General Than Shwe, chairman of the State Law and 
Order 
Restoration Council, SLORC, and commander in chief of the 
Defense Services, at 1000 this morning received the visiting 
Cuban delegation led by Mr. Roberto Robaina Gonzalez, foreign 
minister of the Republic of Cuba, at the Defense Ministry's 
Dagon House. Also present were Lieutenant General Maung Aye, 
deputy commander in chief of the Defense Services and Army 
commander in chief; SLORC Secretary-1 Lt. Gen. Khin Nyunt; SLORC 
Secretary-2 Lt. Gen. Tin U; Foreign Minister U Ohn Gyaw; and 
Protocol Department Director General Thura U Aung Htet. 
  At 1100, the Cuban delegation paid a courtesy call on Deputy 
Prime Minister Vice Admiral Maung Maung Khin at the latter's 
office and held frank and cordial talks on matters relating to 
foreign investment, economic cooperation, and promoting 
bilateral goodwill. 
  At 1430, the visiting delegation called on Trade Minister 
Lt. 
Gen. Tun Kyi at the Trade Ministry and held talks on bilateral 
economic and trade matters. 
  At 1330, the Cuban foreign minister and delegation met and 
held cordial talks on social and economic matters with Burmese 
traders and entrepreneurs at the Union of Myanmar Chamber of 
Commerce and Industry on Bo Son Pet Road. 
  The Cuban foreign minister and delegation this afternoon 
left 
Burma for Cambodia. They were seen off at the airport by 
Foreign Affairs Minister U Ohn Gyaw, Deputy Foreign Affairs 
Minister U Nyunt Swe, and other ranking officials from the 
Ministry of Foreign Affairs. 

</TEXT>

