<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Burma </F>
<H3> <TI>   Khin Nyunt Outlines Police Force Reform </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1503053894 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 1330 GMT 14 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1503053894 </F>
<F P=104>  Rangoon Radio Burma </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Burmese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Lieutenant General Khin Nyunt, secretary-1 of 
the State Law and Order Restoration Council [SLORC], at 1200 
today met with officers of the People's Police Force [PPF] at 
the Ministry of Home Affairs located at the corner of Sethmu-1 
Road and Saya San Road. He discussed PPF work and delivered an 
address. 
  Lt. Gen. Khin Nyunt explained that the major responsibility 
and objectives of the PPF are crime prevention to ensure law and 
order, local peace, and tranquillity; to expose and investigate 
crimes, arrests, and collect evidence against offenders; to take 
legal action; and to provide local security. 
  He said a review of the current state of the PPF shows that 
the time has come to change and reform the law, methods of 
operation, and practices. Therefore, he said, the SLORC has 
formed the Committee To Reform the Administrative System of the 
PPF with ranking officials with a view to reforming the spirit, 
discipline, and methods of operation based on the administrative 
and training system of the entire PPF. The committee will 
review and scrutinize the current system of PPF administration, 
intelligence, legal action procedure, and the PPF training 
system. It will also attempt to promote public trust in the 
PPF, eradicate graft and corruption, prevent the deliberate use 
of power to create hardships for the people, and to eradicate 
undesirable practices inherited from the colonial era. He said 
the committee was empowered to lay down the necessary rules, 
regulations, and procedures to reform the administrative and 
training system of the PPF, amend the existing laws, and enact 
new laws. [passage omitted] 
  In conclusion, he called on the members of the PPF to use 
their mental and physical powers to help reform the PPF 
administrative system. He called on them to get eliminate 
undesirable habits and practices left over from the colonial era 
and to strive to become a PPF well loved by the people. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

