<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK Party Delegation Ends Visit, Departs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1503035494 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 1200 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1503035494 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lao </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hwang Chang-yop, Secretariat member of the Workers 
Party of Korea [WPK], and his delegation left Vientiane for home 
at noon on 13 March after ending a four-day visit to Laos. 
Hwang Chang-yop and the delegation were seen off at Wattai 
Airport by Thongsing Thammavong, Political Bureau member and 
head of the Organizing Committee of the Lao People's 
Revolutionary Party [LPRP] Central Committee. Also on hand to 
see the delegation off at the airport was Chang Yong-chun, 
ambassador extraordinary and plenipotentiary of the DPRK to 
Laos, along with many high-ranking cadres. 
  During the visit to Laos, the WPK delegation led by Hwang 
Chang-yop, Secretariat member of the WPK Central Committee, paid 
a courtesy call on Khamtai Siphandon, chairman of the LPRP 
Central Committee and prime minister, and met with Thongsing 
Thammavong, Political Bureau member and head of the Organizing 
Committee of the party Central Committee. It also visited the 
high-level party and state political training school, the 
construction site of the Lao-Thai friendship bridge, and the 
party unit of the Nam Ngeum hydroelectric dam. 

</TEXT>

