<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cuban Foreign Minister Arrives for Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1203140294 Vientiane KPL in English 0904 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1203140294 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane KPL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, March 12 (KPL) -- Cuban Foreign Minister 
Roberto Robaina Gonzalez, who is also Politburo member of the 
Communist Party of Cuba Central Committee, yesterday evening 
arrived here on a two-day official visit to Lao PDR [People's 
Democratic Republic] at the invitation of his Lao counterpart, 
Somsavat Lengsavat. The Cuban foreign minister with his 
delegation was warmly greeted at the Wattai airport by Lao 
Foreign Minister Somsavat Lengsavat and senior officials of the 
Foreign Ministry. Cuban Ambassador to Laos Ricardo Danza Sigas 
was also present at the welcoming ceremony. 
  The two foreign ministers together with their delegations 
held talks at the Lan Xang hotel on the same evening. At the 
talks, the sides informed each other of the developments in 
their respective countries and the further strengthening of 
their bilateral relations and cooperation. They also agreed to 
renew their cooperation on a mutual benefit basis. The Cuban 
side showed interest in small hydro-power generation, large 
scale cattle breeding for export, cooperation in public health, 
sugar cane plantation and sugar production in Laos in the future. 

</TEXT>

