<H3> <TI>   IPR Enforcement Committee Set Up </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1503124394 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 0530 GMT 
15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1503124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Thai </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Police Department is cooperating with the 
Commerce Ministry in suppressing intellectual property rights 
[IPR] violations by setting up a working committee with 
authority to arrest any offenders. 
  Deputy Commerce Minister Churin Laksanawisit says that the 
Police Department director general has set up a committee 
comprising 37 police officers nationwide to suppress 
intellectual property rights violations. The committee is 
chaired by Police General Winit Charoensiri, deputy police 
director general for suppression. The cooperation shows the 
Thai Government's sincerity in suppressing intellectual property 
violations. 

</TEXT>

