<H3> <TI>   Minister Previews Burma Visit, Gas Deal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1503024494 Bangkok BANGKOK POST in English 15 Mar 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> BK1503024494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok BANGKOK POST </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Industry Minister Sanan Khachonprasat will visit 
Rangoon next month to witness the signing of a Memorandum of 
Understanding [MoU] if a deal to purchase gas from Burma is 
completed. Negotiations between the Petroleum Authority of 
Thailand and Burmese government to buy natural gas from the 
Martabang site are expected to be settled this month, said 
Maj-Gen Sanan vesterday. The gas project covers two exploratory 
plots, M5 and M6, over an area of 26,140 square metres. 
  France's Total Co Ltd has been developing the site since 
1992 
with Unocal Myanmar Co holding shares in the company. 
  "The Burmese side would like to have the minister witness 
the 
MoU signing after the deal is settled, as far as I know," said 
Thai Ambassador to Rangoon Wirasak Futrakun by telephone. 
  Maj-Gen Sanan said he would also meet privately with Burmese 
Forestry Minister Lt-Gen Chit Swe to discuss an extension to the 
timeframe during which Thai companies can remove felled logs 
still in Burmese territory. 

</TEXT>

