<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   Group Warns of More Abductions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1503064094 Quezon City Radio Filipinas in English 0230 GMT 
15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1503064094 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City Radio Filipinas </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A breakaway group of the MNLF [Moro National 
Liberation Front] operating in Basilan province in southern 
Philippines has warned that more wealthy businessmen and school 
teachers will be abducted by the group. Sulaiman Ali, leader of 
one of the lost commands said the new wave of kidnapping will 
start at the close of the Muslim holy month of Ramadan. The 
month-long fasting of Muslims ended on Sunday. 
  Ali, however, denied responsibility in the kidnapping of 
five 
school teachers in Tuburan, Basilan last 7 March. He demanded a 
pull out of the marines from Tuburan, saying that more people 
will be abducted by his group starting this month if the marine 
troops will not be pulled out. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

