<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK Diplomat in PRC Cited on IAEA Inspection </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1503093594 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0900 GMT 15 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1503093594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["AP, YONHAP report from Beijing"] </F>
  [Text] The North Korean side admitted on 15 March that 
there were some disputes regarding the International Atomic 
Energy Agency's [IAEA] method of inspecting its nuclear 
facilities, but revealed that such friction can be resolved 
through dialogue. 
  (Choe Han-chun), councillor of the DPRK Embassy in Beijing, 
said that the inspection team demanded that it take samples from 
one facility, but the North Korean authorities rejected this 
move, calling it an unjust demand. 
  Councillor Choe said that there was a slight dispute in the 
process of inspection, but that it is not serious. He also 
claimed that this can be resolved through dialogue between North 
Korea and the IAEA. 

</TEXT>

