<H3> <TI>   Further on Efforts Toward N-S Envoy Exchange </TI></H3>
<H4>   Steps for Next Contact Discussed </H4>
<F P=102> SK1503024594 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0202 GMT 15 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1503024594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This morning, the government held a strategic 
meeting participated by unification-related ministries, and 
chaired by Yi Yong-tok, vice prime minister and national 
unification board minister, to discuss follow-up measures for 
the seventh North-South working-level contact for the exchange 
of special envoys scheduled to be held on 16 March. 
  At today's meeting, the government confirmed the position 
that the exchange of special envoys must be carried out before 
the third round of U.S.-North Korean high-level talks is held. 
It has decided to call on the North side to make efforts to 
expedite the process of initiating exchange of special envoys 
during tomorrow's contact in Panmunjom. 
  During tomorrow's contact, if there is no final agreement 
between the North and South, and see only a negative attitude of 
the North side, the government will officially ask the United 
States to postpone the third round of U.S.-North Korean 
high-level talks. 
  The government has decided that if the International Atomic 
Energy Agency's inspection in North Korea which ended on 15 
March, does not produce sufficient resuslt, the government is 
considering to resume the Team Spirit exercise. 

</TEXT>

