<H3> <TI>   Agreement Signed With PRC on Public Officials </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1503063694 Seoul YONHAP in English 0528 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1503063694 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, March 15 (YONHAP) -- South Korea's Government 
Administration Ministry and China's Personnel Ministry signed an 
agreement Tuesday [15 March] on exchanges and training of public 
officials. 
  The agreement promotes bilateral visits, business trips and 
training for public officials and, as a start, Seoul and Beijing 
will exchange about 15 division director-level officials taking 
part in a training program this year. 
  In addition, the two countries will exchange administrative 
information such as government publications and provide 
conveniences for each other's officials under the reciprocity 
principle. 
  The agreement was signed during a visit to Beijing by Son 
Chong, director-general of the Central Officials Training 
Institute. 

</TEXT>

