<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ex-President's Funds Transferred to Treasury </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1403114994 Seoul YONHAP in English 0644 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1403114994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, March 14 (YONHAP) -- Former President Chon 
Tu-hwan's "donation" of political funds totaling 14 billion won 
(17.5 million U.S. dollars), including 100 million won in 
interest, to the government, had been transferred to the 
national treasury as of April 25, 1989, Board of Audit and 
Inspection (BAI) officials said Monday [14 March]. 
  Precisely what happened to the funds is not known because 
national treasury funds are channeled, irrespective of their 
source, into the government's fiscal plan, the officials said. 
  The BAI looked into whether Chon's donation was placed in 
the 
national treasury at the request of the opposition Democratic 
Party during the recent parliamentary session. 

</TEXT>

