<H3> <TI>   Hosokawa Urges Larger Deregulation Items List </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1503061394 Tokyo KYODO in English 0550 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1503061394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 15 KYODO -- Prime Minister Morihiro 
Hosokawa called on his ministers Tuesday to come up with a list 
of new items for possible deregulation by the end of the month, 
government officials said. 
  Hosokawa made the call in a morning cabinet meeting in 
response to pressure from the United States and elsewhere for 
Japan to harmonize its economy with that of the rest of the 
world. 
  In the Japan-U.S. trade framework negotiations, Washington 
has proposed dozens of new targets for deregulation. 
  Hosokawa called deregulation a vital component of the 
government's economic reforms and said it must be actively 
tackled to promote harmonious economic relations with other 
countries. 

</TEXT>

