<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 14 KYODO -- Norwegian parliamentary 
leader Kristi Kolle Grondahl Monday [14 March] met Prime 
Minister Morihiro Hosokawa for an exchange of greetings and a 
brief discussion of Russia's disposal of radioactive waste into 
the Sea of Japan. 
  Grondahl, president of the 165-member Storting, remarked 
that 
Norway faces a similar problem with Russian nuclear dumping near 
its own borders, government officials said. 
  She said Prime Minister Gro Harlem Brundtland, who canceled 
plans to visit Japan in January because of a cold, hopes to 
visit in the near future to discuss the problem. 
  Hosokawa said Foreign Minister Tsutomu Hata plans to raise 
the issue when he visits Russia this month. 
  Grondahl is visiting Japan at the invitation of the House of 
Councillors. 

