<H3> <TI>   FTC Raids Warehouse Firms Suspected in Cartel </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1503135694 Tokyo KYODO in English 1208 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1503135694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 15 KYODO -- The Fair Trade Commission 
(FTC) raided the office of the Japan Association of Refrigerated 
Warehouses and about 20 warehouse companies Tuesday [15 March] 
for allegedly operating an unauthorized cartel, officials said. 
Nichirei Corp., unrivaled leader in the refrigeration warehouse 
industry and also No. 1 in frozen foods, and Yokohama Reito Co., 
the nation's second largest cold storage company, were among the 
firms searched by the government fair trade watchdog. 
  The FTC suspect the association and the companies illegally 
conspired in July 1992 to fix storage fees and the timing of the 
increase before hiking the fees from July until the end of the 
year in violation of the antimonopoly law. 

</TEXT>

