Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 15 KYODO -- Japan's top economic 
planner on Tuesday [15 March] called for more public works 
spending, particularly housing investment, to give an added 
boost to the burgeoning economic recovery. 
  The Japanese economy is showing some sign of pickup in such 
areas as housing, home electric appliances, audio equipment and 
autos, Manae Kubota, director general of the Economic Planning 
Agency [EPA], told a regular press conference. 
  The bud of the economic recovery should be nurtured with 
steps to spur personal spending, such as more housing investment 
and early implementation of planned tax cuts, she said. 
  These measures will be effective in putting the economy on a 
strong recovery track, she said. 

