<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further MNLF Talks Set </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1503063894 Quezon City Radio Filipinas in English 0230 GMT 
14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1503063894 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City Radio Filipinas </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The second round of formal peace talks between the 
government and the Moro National Liberation Front [MNLF] will be 
held in Jakarta, Indonesia. The talks beginning 13 to 22 April 
this year will focus on the substantive portions of the Tripoli 
Agreement of 1976. They will also take up the reports by the 
joint working groups, joint cease-fire committee, and the mixed 
committee set up during the first formal talks last November, 
also in Indonesia. 
  MNLF Chairman Nur Misuari said he remains optimistic about 
the outcome of the peace talks. Misuari was interviewed by 
reporters in Sulu, where he delivered a message of peace at a 
mosque in Jolo. 

</TEXT>

