<H3> <TI>   FTC Orders 15 Paint Makers To Pay Fines </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1603093694 Tokyo KYODO in English 0835 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1603093694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 16 KYODO -- The Fair Trade Commission 
(FTC) has ordered 15 paint manufacturers to pay 470 million yen 
in fines for operating an unauthorized cartel, FTC officials 
said Wednesday [16 March]. Among the firms fined by the FTC, 
Atom Chemical Paint Co. was ordered to pay 87 million yen, 
Hitachi Chemical Co. 70 million yen and Sekisui Jushi Corp. 51 
million yen. 
  According to the FTC, the companies concluded an 
unauthorized 
cartel in October 1990 that served as a front for bid-rigging 
activities and manipulated the price of paint until December 
1991. In December 1992, the FTC ordered the firms to stop the 
unfair practice. 

</TEXT>

