<F P=102>  OW1703064294 Tokyo KYODO in English 0606 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1703064294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 17 KYODO -- Japan's corporate pretax 
profits for the October-December quarter slid 6.2 percent from a 
year before, declining for the 14th straight quarter, the 
Finance Ministry said Thursday [17 March]. 
  The pretax profits for manufacturing companies fell 16.5 
percent, while those for nonmanufacturers increased 3.9 percent, 
the ministry said. 
  Combined sales dropped 1.4 percent, suffering the seventh 
consecutive quarter of decline from year-earlier levels. 
  Corporate capital investment during the reporting quarter 
shrank 16.8 percent, for the eighth straight quarterly decline 
from year-earlier levels. 

