<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Discusses APEC Agenda </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1703072294 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 0530 GMT 
17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1703072294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Thai </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Finance Minister Tharin Nimmanhemin says it has 
been agreed that the meeting of APEC [Asia-Pacific Economic 
Cooperation] finance ministers, to be held during 18-19 March in 
Hawaii, will discuss economic growth strategies, the role of 
revolving funds in national development, and the development of 
local financial markets. It has also been agreed that the 
meeting will not be used for forced access to financial markets 
or examination of a country's economic policies. He said that 
he would head the seminar on the topic of the role of revolving 
funds in national development. 
  The finance minister disclosed that his delegation has been 
changed to include a representative of the office of the 
securities exchange management committee to cover the meeting's 
agenda. The delegation originally included only representatives 
of the Finance Ministry and the Bank of Thailand. 

</TEXT>

