<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Thai Delegation Visit, Leadership Meetings Noted </TI></H3>
<H4>   Chuan Meets Do Muoi </H4>
<F P=102> BK1603145294 Hanoi VNA in English 1429 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1603145294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA March 16 -- Prime Minister Chuan Likphai 
and his party called on Communist Party of Vietnam General 
Secretary Do Muoi here this afternoon. 
  During their meeting, the two leaders informed each other of 
the developments in their countries and noted with pleasure that 
the Vietnamese-Thai friendly and cooperative ties were being 
developed favourably and that the recent exchange of visits of 
high-level delegations of the two countries ushered in a new 
chapter in their bilateral relations. 
  Party Secretary Do Muoi affirmed that Vietnam would continue 
its efforts to strengthen and develop the friendly, neighboury 
and cooperative relations with Thailand in the interests of the 
two peoples, and for peace, stability and development in 
Southeast Asia and the world as a whole. 
  Prime Minister Chuan Likphai, for his part, expressed his 
desire to further promote the cooperation between Thailand and 
Vietnam by strictly implementing the agreements reached by the 
two governments and going on with discussions to solve remaining 
issues in the spirit of friendship, constructive cooperation and 
mutual benefits. 
  On this occasion, General Sectary Do Muoi asked P.M. Chuan 
Likphai to convey his best wishes to the king and the whole 
royal family of Thailand. 

</TEXT>

