<H3> <TI>   Thai Delegation Visit, Leadership Meetings Noted </TI></H3>
<H4>   Chuan Speaks at Banquet </H4>
<F P=102> BK1703054494 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 0000 GMT 
17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1703054494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Thai </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Speech by Prime Minister Chuan Likphai at a banquet held in </F>
his honor by SRV Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet in Hanoi on 16 March 
-- recorded] 
  [Excerpts] [passage omitted] I am very pleased to learn 
that our countries have closely cooperated with each other in 
financial services and investment markets. The Bank of Thailand 
and the Securities Exchange of Thailand will render cooperation 
to and closely coordinate with the Vietnamese national bank. 
Such exchanges of experience and information will help 
strengthen the financial services of the two countries. I 
believe we all agree that the present world economic system will 
advance firmly if we can build up and develop a strong base in 
financial services. We must be prepared for rapidly increasing 
competition. The cooperation which exists under the principle 
of good understanding and mutual benefit will form an important 
foundation for multilateral relations, which will lead to a 
collaboration of quality power [khunaphap phalang]. I believe 
that good relations among the countries in the region, 
especially the countries in the Mekong River basin, will enable 
us to cope with problems that may arise in sharing the use of 
natural resources. We will work to jointly preserve and improve 
the environment to benefit our present and future generations. 
[passage omitted] 
  During my visit to Vietnam, leading figures from business 
institutions in major fields are joining the trip so they will 
be directly informed of certain policies of both Thailand and 
Vietnam that will promote trade and investment. This will 
create mutual benefit within a definite framework and 
regulations. They will be able to observe the economic 
potential of Vietnam. Furthermore, both sides must carry out 
necessary activities to promote trade and investment cooperation 
by supplying each other with clear and correct information. 
Therefore, I am pleased that Thai and Vietnamese investment 
promotion organizations have jointly organized a seminar to seek 
ways to further expand trade and investment cooperation. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

