the time of "presidential elections" people who account for 
nearly 20 percent of the total number of electors boycotted 
voting to express their opposition to Kim Yong-sam. This 
virtually means that more than two thirds of the population 
voted against him. Thus, the Kim Yong-sam puppet regime had a 
gloomy future from the first step as it came into being amidst 
opposition and rejection by an overwhelming majority of the 
people. 
  The Kim Yong-sam puppet clique also took upon itself a 
timebomb by getting into the same boat with the preceding 
military dictators. For the traitor Kim Yong-sam to join hands 
with the military dictatorial forces denounced by the people was 
an act of turning his back on the people, and for him to promise 
those forces to "protect" them after his assumption of office 
was an unpardonable criminal act. 
  After putting up the "civilian" signboard the Kim Yong-sam 
puppet clique honored its commitment to the preceding military 
dictatorial forces, while breaking all his "promises" to the 
people. That is why the South Korean people view "in the same 
light" Chun Doo hwan- No Tae-u clique, a target of purge and 
punishment, and the traitor Kim Yong-sam who is zealously 
defending them. 
  The traitor's much-touted, fine-sounding "civilian politics" 
has punctured. It is as clear as noonday what fate will befall 
him. 

