Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The new Sabah chief minister to replace Datuk Joseph 
Pairin Kitingan is scheduled to be sworn in this afternoon. The 
national news agency BERNAMA said in Kota Kinabalu that it has 
received a fax from the Information Department inviting newsmen 
to cover the ceremony at 3.30 pm [0730 GMT] at the palace in the 
state capital. The department's press (?advisory) confirmed the 
widespread talks that Datuk Pairin would step down this 
afternoon. 
  Sabah National Front chief Tan Sri Sakaran Dandai is set to 
become chief minister. 
  Yesterday, the National Front, BN, staked its claim to form 
the new Sabah Government by petitioning the governor, Tun 
Mohamed Said Keruak, that it now commanded the majority in the 
State Legislative Assembly. There are altogether 30 state 
assemblymen, including those from the Sabah United Party, PBS, 
who defected to the National Front, filed the petition to those 
who respected the governor to ask Datuk Pairin to step down and 
offer the post to Tan Sri Sakaran. [sentence as heard] 

