<F P=101> Australia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Indonesia To Take Part in Military Exercise </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1603093094 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0500 GMT 
16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1603093094 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Soldiers from Indonesia and Australia are to take 
part in military exercises over the next four weeks. A team of 
25 Australian soldiers from the Special Air Service will take 
part in Exercise Night Komodo in Indonesia. At the same time, a 
contingent from Indonesia's special forces will undergo training 
in Australia's Exercise Kookaburra. 
  A statement from the Australian Defense Department said the 
training will concentrate on basic military skills relevant to 
special forces, including weapons practice, parachuting, 
navigation, and communications. The department said Indonesian 
troops would use Australian facilities in Perth to train to 
retake an aircraft after a hijack. 

</TEXT>

