<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Thai Delegation Visit, Leadership Meetings Noted </TI></H3>
<H4>   Kiet Welcomes Chuan, Agreements Signed </H4>
<F P=102> BK1603142294 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1100 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1603142294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Vietnamese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Dinh Khai on the ceremony held in Hanoi on the </F>
morning of 16 March to welcome Thai Prime Minister Chuan Likphai 
-- recorded] 
  [Summary] At 1130 sharp, the motorcade escorting Prime 
Minister Chuan Likphai and other distinguished Thai guests 
arrived at the Presidential Palace. On hand to welcome Prime 
Minister Chuan and his entourage were Prime Minister Vo Van 
Kiet; Deputy Prime Minister Tran Duc Luong; Foreign Minister 
Nguyen Manh Cam; Le Xuan Trinh, minister and director of the 
Government Office; Dau Ngoc Xuan, minister and director of the 
State Committee for Cooperation and Investment; Vietnamese 
Ambassador to Thailand Le Cong Phung; Le At Hoi, chairman of the 
Hanoi City People's Committee; and many leading officials of 
various ministries, departments, sectors, and mass organizations 
at the central level and in Hanoi. Also present at the 
welcoming ceremony were members of the diplomatic corps, 
representatives of international organizations in Hanoi, and 
many Vietnamese and foreign journalists. 
  "As the motorcade stopped, Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet walked 
to the door of the limousine carrying Prime Minister Chuan 
Likphai to greet him. Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet then invited 
Chuan to join him on the honorary stand while the military band 
played the national anthems of Thailand and Vietnam." Next, 
Prime Minister Chuan Likphai reviewed the guard of honor before 
being introduced to Vietnamese officials, members of the 
diplomatic corps, and representatives of international 
organizations in Hanoi. 
  "Immediately following the official welcoming ceremony, 
Prime 
Minister Vo Van Kiet cordially received Prime Minister Chuan 
Likphai at the Presidential Palace. On behalf of the Vietnamese 
Government, Vo Van Kiet welcomed Chuan and his entourage on 
their official visit to Vietnam. He highly valued the visit and 
expressed his belief that this event will contribute to 
promoting cooperative ties between the two countries in the days 
ahead. 
  "In his reply speech, Chuan thanked Vo Van Kiet and the 
Vietnamese Government and people for according his delegation a 
very warm welcome. He said: We have waited a long time for 
this opportunity to visit Vietnam and we are convinced that this 
event will further strengthen the good relations between the two 
countries. 
  "The talks between the Vietnamese Government delegation 
headed by Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet and the Thai Government 
delegation headed by Prime Minister Chuan Likphai took place at 
the Presidential Palace this afternoon. The two sides informed 
each other about the situation in each country and exchanged 
views on issues of common concern in a bid to further develop 
the friendly and cooperative ties between the two countries. 
  "A ceremony was held immediately following the talks to sign 
agreements on tourist cooperation and cooperation between the 
Vietnam Chamber of Commerce and Industry and the Federation of 
Thai Industries." 

</TEXT>

