<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tokyo To Reveal Market-Opening Measures in Jul </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1603040694 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 16 
Mar 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1603040694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 16 March Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] In a news conference on the evening of 15 March, 
Chief Cabinet Secretary Masayoshi Takemura spoke about the 
voluntary market-liberalization measures for resolving the 
Japanese-U.S. economic disputes and said that the finalized 
measures will be revealed at the Japanese-U.S. summit meeting to 
be held at the time of the industrialized nations summit in July 
(Naples summit). He added that drastic tax reform plans will 
compose part of the macroeconomic measures. 
  Takemura said, "Market-liberalization measures should 
naturally contain macroeconomic measures, and my understanding 
is that the tax reform plans will be part of them." 
  He also said 1) the government's plan is to bring the 
Japanese- U.S. economic framework talks to a conclusion by June 
and that it needs to come up with an idea on what position to 
take on tax cuts for next year and thereafter; and 2) the 
government will finalize its policy after confirming the views 
of the ruling parties. 

</TEXT>

