------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


<H5>  Decline in Support Rate for LDP President Kono </H5>
  In the January survey, the support rate for coalition 
parties 
again surpassed that for the LDP. The decline in support for 
the LDP over a long span is remarkable. Mr. Yohei Kono has been 
elected the LDP president to win broad support for 
reconstructing the party. 
  Yet, the support rate for President Kono is also showing 
constant decline. In particular, he is unpopular among female 
voters. Although 33 percent of male voters support him, the 
support rate remained at only 23.5 percent among the female 
voters. 


Table 4. Q: The government has recently determined partial liberalization of 
the rice market. Do you agree with the decision? 

