<H5>  Public Attitude Toward Rice Market Liberalization </H5>
  What are the public's reactions to the Hosokawa 
administration's decision on partial liberalization of the rice 
market? According to the survey result, 49 percent were for, 
and 34 percent against the decision. Since the cabinet support 
rate did not drop by the strong opposition to the rice 
liberalization decision, it appears the issue had not been 
regarded as a hot controversy. As a matter of course, the 
farmers-fishermen group reacted most strongly to the decision. 
However, it is very interesting that the Hosokawa cabinet 
retained high support (49 percent in December, and 50 percent in 
January) even among those who opposed the rice liberalization. 
It seems that, even among farmers, the rice liberalization is 
no longer a controversy to affect their confidence in the 
cabinet. 


