<H5>  Pollees' Voting-Intentions </H5>
  Since the political turnover in last August, the decline in 
the LDP's popularity is noteworthy in the survey on voting 
intentions. When we started surveying public attitude toward the 
question of Table 5, the support for the LDP always exceeded 50 
percent. But the figure dropped to just a little over 20 
percent in the latest survey. In contrast, the JNP and other 
coalition parties are steadily gaining voters' support. In the 
January survey, Shinseito obtained public support ranking with 
the SDPJ. 
  NOTE: The survey, conducted by Chuo Research Inc. on 7-10 
January, was carried on as individual interviews of 2,000 
eligible voters picked at random. Responses were obtained from 
69.3 percent of, or 1,385, pollees. Data belong to the 
Multipurpose Statistic Databank of Tsukuba University. 

