------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


<H5>  Support for SDPJ Also Unchanged </H5>
  It is said that the SDPJ lost public support when a lot of 
rebels contributed to the upper house's rejection of the 
political reform bills, and that it then won back popularity by 
saying no to the public welfare tax. Such moves were not 
observed in our monthly survey on the SDPJ support rate. In the 
February survey, the support rate for the coalition dropped by 4 
percentage points from the previous month, and this was as low 
as that for the LDP. In particular, Shinseito's popularity 
sharply declined. 


