<H5>  Public Perceptions of Living Conditions </H5>
  While it is believed Japan is still experiencing recession, 
voters' perceptions of their own living conditions were not very 
bad in the last 12 months. Over 60 percent answered their 
living conditions remain unchanged, and 35.5 percent said they 
are facing difficulties in making their living. These figures 
are a little better than those in December 1993. While the 
public is very concerned about the prolonged recession, it 
probably does not seriously impact on the living of individuals. 


