<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sirivut on Khmer Rouge, Investment, MFN </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1803105294 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0500 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1803105294 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0500 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On the afternoon of 17 March, Prince Kromkhun 
Norodom Sirivut, deputy prime minister and minister of foreign 
affairs and international cooperation, received a delegation 
from the Organization for Consolidating International Ethics led 
by Mrs. (Verney Pan), chairman of the Organization for 
Consolidating International Ethics in Cambodia. 
  On this occasion, the prince kromkhun welcomed the 
delegation 
and talked about the elections in Cambodia two years ago, which 
were successful because of the correct implementation of the 
Paris agreement, particularly under the leadership of His 
Majesty King Norodom Sihanouk. It was also due to the 
participation of the Cambodian people nationwide. 
  Answering his guests' questions on the Khmer Rouge and 
investment in Cambodia, the prince kromkhun said that the Khmer 
Rouge issue is of no importance to the Royal Government as long 
as this group refuses to abide by the national reconciliation 
principles. On the investment issue, the United States will 
soon grant Cambodia favorable trading status. Cambodia will 
always welcome foreign investors who want to do business in the 
Kingdom of Cambodia. 

</TEXT>

