<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Radio Reports on Pailin Fighting 14-16 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1803075994 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1803075994 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] News from the Pailin battlefield on 14, 15, and 16 
March: 
  1. On 14, 15, and 16 March the communist Vietnamese 
puppets continued their assault on the Pailin region from the 
south and the north using tanks, artillery, and infantry troops. 
  2. We destroyed four of the raiding forces' T-54 tanks on 
14 March; one at Treng, two at Sdau, and another at Kamping Puoy. 
  3. We killed 60 infantry troops of the communist 
Vietnamese puppets on 15 March and wounded several others, who 
were dragged away by their comrades. We seized 85 firearms, 
including AK's, B- 40's, RPK's, SKS's, and AR-15's. 
  4. At 1030 on 15 March, we hit a communist Vietnamese 
puppet plane over Chineang along Route 10. The plane was forced 
to turn back hastily and land at Battambang to avoid becoming 
another of the many carcasses on the Pailin battlefield. The 
people have a great predilection for the wreckage of the 
communist Vietnamese puppet planes; they make good knives, pots, 
and pans. 
  5. We hit them hard on 16 March, killing 49 raiding 
troops, wounding 60 others, and destroying another T-54 tank. 
  In sum, over these three days of fighting we destroyed five 
T-54 tanks, killed 109 raiding troops, and wounded 60 others. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

