<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Khamtai Sends Message to DPRK's Kim Il-song </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1703132094 Vientiane KPL in English 0859 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1703132094 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane KPL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, March 17 (KPL) -- Khamtai Siphandon, 
president of the LPRP CC [Lao People's Revolutionary Party 
Central Committee] and prime minister of the Lao PDR [People's 
Democratic Republic], has sent a message of thanks to Kim 
Il-song, general secretary of the Worker's Party of Korea and 
president of the DPR [Democratic People's Republic] of Korea for 
the best wishes extended to the Lao leader on the occasion of 
his 70th birthday. 
  The Lao prime minister expressed thanks for the kind and 
meaningful words conveyed to the Lao party, state and people, as 
well as President Kim Il-song's assessment of the relationship 
and cooperation between the two parties, states and leaders of 
the two countries. 
  "With goodwill and determination of the two sides, I do hope 
that the friendly relations, and the cooperation between the two 
parties, states and people based on the same ideal would be 
further developed," wrote the message. 
  The message also wished the Korean leader good heath, long 
life, and success in the tasks of leading Korean people in the 
construction of socialism and in the reunification of the Korean 
peninsula. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

